ESTIMATION OF BUSINESS EXPENSES
INTRODUCTION
OVERVIEW
This involves estimating all the expenses required to start and
operate the business, such as equipment,rent,inventory,and
marketing.By calculating these costs upfront,business owners can
better plan their budget and avoid unexpected expenses.
PURPOSE
Estimates are important because they allow businesses to set
expectations for their customers.They also help businesses determine
whether or not a project is feasible and how mach profit they can
expect to make.
PROBLEM DEFINITION & DESIGN THINKING
EMPATHY MAP
IDEATION & BRAINSTORMING
RESULT
ADVANTAGES & DISADVANTAGES
ADVATAGES
 Increased understanding of costs.
 For funding requirements.
 To understand material requirements.
 To aid reconstitution.
 To know equipment and tooling requirements.
 To pre-plan labour requirements.
 To understand the cost to benefit ratio.
 To understand rebuild costs for a valuation.
DISADVENTAGES
 The estimate cannot communicate between labor and supervisor.
 Changing the method of estimation does not maintain the quality of
the material.
 Good efficiency cannot be achieved with every task.
 Certain types of overhead costs cannot be controlled.
APPLACTIONS
A formula for calculating expenses in a business is : Total Expenses =
Costs of Goods Sold (COGS)+Operating Expenses.
CONCLUSION
In Conclusion,cost estimation is an important component of project
management that ensures projects are finished on schedule and within
budget.
FUTURE SCOPE
Cost estimation in project management is the process forecasting the
financial and other resources needed to complete a project within
defined scope.
